hen peopl) Tj463.68 0  TD -0.1555  Tc 0.0355  Tw (e ) Tj-463.68 -11.52  TD -0.0951  Tc 0.6733  Tw (give themselves to do what God wants them to do. The Sabbath was broken in this small incident, the carrying of a ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0691  Tc 1.1251  Tw (sleeping mat. It is this small offence that brings out Jesus\222 \223greater transgression\224: the healing of a person on the ) TjT* -0.1575  Tc 3.3975  Tw (Sabbath. And it leads) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj98.88 0  TD -0.1172  Tc 2.9142  Tw (to God\222s greatest breaking of the Sabbath in raising the dead. The enemy recognized) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-98.88 -11.52  TD -0.0789  Tc 1.4554  Tw (immediately where things began to go wrong! The command \223Pick up your mat\224 is confrontational. Jesus could ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1239  Tc 0.6553  Tw (have told the man to leave his mat and come back the next day. Bu) Tj271.2 0  TD -0.0876  Tc 0.4476  Tw (t He wanted him to break the Sabbath in order to ) Tj-271.2 -11.52  TD -0.0825  Tc -0.0375  Tw (demonstrate what the Sabbath was all about. ) Tj178.08 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-142.08 -11.52  TD -0.0888  Tc 0.373  Tw (The third order \223walk\224 is also important. Jesus did not say \223dance\224 or \223run.\224 The word \223walk\224 is frequently ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0467  Tc 0.8867  Tw (used in Scripture, often in the context of going toget) Tj216 0  TD -0.0904  Tc 0.9304  Tw (her. \223Enoch walked with God\224) Tj125.76 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (131) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.094  Tc 0.774  Tw ( And \223Noah was a righteous ) Tj-351.84 -11.52  TD -0.0969  Tc 1.5369  Tw (man, blameless among the people of his time, and he walked with God.\224) Tj304.32 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (132) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0632  Tc 1.2032  Tw ( We are not supposed to walk alone. ) Tj-314.4 -11.52  TD -0.079  Tc 1.3117  Tw (Walking is a form of fellowship. The man, obviously, did not understand) Tj303.36 0  TD -0.0502  Tc 0.7835  Tw ( this, as is clear from what follows. The ) Tj-303.36 -11.52  TD -0.0698  Tc 1.0559  Tw (word \223walk\224 also applies God\222s dealing with us. We are raised from the dead in order to take up that task that is ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0442  Tc -0.0758  Tw (given to us and to walk through life with Him. ) Tj186.72 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-150.72 -11.52  TD -0.1175  Tc 0.9575  Tw (This incident took place on the Sabbath. The Jews ha) Tj216.96 0  TD -0.0719  Tc 0.6065  Tw (d a valid reason to protest that carrying one\222s mat on ) Tj-252.96 -11.52  TD -0.1005  Tc 1.6845  Tw (the Sabbath was labor, which was forbidden by the law. The man justified his transgression by linking it to his ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0975  Tc 1.4175  Tw (healing. He had obeyed Jesus\222 command to get up, which brought about his healing; consequ) Tj387.36 0  TD -0.1803  Tc 0.7803  Tw (ently, he obeyed the ) Tj-387.36 -11.52  TD -0.0934  Tc 1.7334  Tw (command to carry his mat. The Jews tried to separate one from the other. They tried to ignore the healing and ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0792  Tc 0.8101  Tw (concentrate on the carrying of the mat. It turns out that this could not be done; the two were inseparable. The only ) TjT* 0.0397  Tc 0  Tw (justific) Tj28.32 0  TD -0.0693  Tc 1.0053  Tw (ation for the breaking of the Sabbath was the healing. For this reason, Jesus assumed all the blame for His ) Tj-28.32 -11.52  TD -0.0959  Tc 0.3873  Tw (command to break the Sabbath, and He clarified that He was the one responsible for the breaking of the Sabbath, not ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1443  Tc 0.8472  Tw (the man who was healed. The man ) Tj144.48 0  TD -0.0844  Tc 0.5944  Tw (could have done little else but to obey. Once he obeyed the command to get up, ) Tj-144.48 -11.52  TD -0.1125  Tc -0.0075  Tw (he also had to obey the command to carry his mat. He had to keep on obeying.  ) Tj312.48 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-276.48 -11.04  TD /F2 10.08  Tf0.0674  Tc 0.7726  Tw (The Pulpit Comme