ic ministry. Rumors about it ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0772  Tc 0.9172  Tw (must have penetrated Bethesda also but at that) Tj189.6 0  TD -0.1161  Tc 0.7715  Tw ( time the man may not have seen any connection between the stories ) Tj-189.6 -11.52  TD -0.1074  Tc 0.9474  Tw (and the coming of this stranger. Added to this, the personal faith of this man hardly played any role in his healing. ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0472  Tc -0.0728  Tw (He was restored to full health by an unilateral act of God, exclusively) Tj275.04 0  TD -0.0905  Tc -0.0295  Tw ( by the faith of the Lord Jesus. ) Tj121.92 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-360.96 -11.52  TD -0.1045  Tc 1.0857  Tw (We also see that Jesus avoided publicity. He disappeared in the crowd immediately after the healing. The ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.1148  Tc 0.401  Tw (man who had been healed had had no time to see who had healed him. As soon as he got up, he was alone. The Lord ) Tj0 -11.52  TD 0.0794  Tc 0.7606  Tw (did n) Tj20.64 0  TD -0.0939  Tc 0.6139  Tw (ot remain at his side to help him digest all that had happened. The man\222s reaction to his healing, however, was ) Tj-20.64 -11.52  TD -0.0885  Tc 0.4049  Tw (very healthy; his first visit is to the temple. We read that Jesus found him there later. The man must have understood ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1236  Tc 0.8676  Tw (that his healing was a di) Tj98.88 0  TD -0.0985  Tc 0.4318  Tw (rect intervention in his life by the hand of God. He was, evidently, not that lonely! Jesus did ) Tj-98.88 -11.52  TD -0.0895  Tc 0.6241  Tw (not let him go completely either. The encounter in the temple was not a coincidence. And we see that Jesus kept on ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1117  Tc 0.5317  Tw (backing up this man while he is being accused) Tj186.24 0  TD -0.0822  Tc 0.4053  Tw (. He took all the responsibility of what had happened upon Himself. It ) Tj-186.24 -11.52  TD -0.108  Tc 1.5323  Tw (wasn\222t the man who broke the Sabbath by doing work; it was the Lord. He is the accused and H