His suffering and death. He became the mud that opened our eyes. ) Tj410.88 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-374.88 -11.52  TD -0.0678  Tc 0.3744  Tw (This man believed Jesus to the point that he foll) Tj192.96 0  TD -0.0407  Tc -0.0793  Tw (owed His instructions to go to Siloam and wash himself. He ) Tj-228.96 -11.52  TD -0.0823  Tc 0.3051  Tw (may not have fully understood what happened but he accepted the humiliation that Jesus put on him. It was, after all, ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0576  Tc 0.5776  Tw (humiliating. It is easy to speak piously about outward manifestations of an inw) Tj320.16 0  TD -0.0691  Tc 0.4291  Tw (ard condition but a blind beggar also ) Tj-320.16 -11.52  TD -0.1142  Tc 0.9542  Tw (needs self) Tj39.84 0  TD 0.0034  Tc 0  Tw (-) Tj3.36 0  TD -0.0986  Tc 0.8243  Tw (respect. We don\222t know how far it was to Siloam and how many people laughed at the man on the way. ) Tj-43.2 -11.52  TD -0.0872  Tc 0.9958  Tw (Maybe nobody did but that did not alleviate the humiliation. Yet, the man did as he was told and in doing th) Tj446.4 0  TD -0.1038  Tc 0.4638  Tw (is, he ) Tj-446.4 -11.52  TD -0.1556  Tc 0.0356  Tw (came back seeing. ) Tj73.44 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-37.44 -11.52  TD -0.0685  Tc 0.6385  Tw (John\222s explanation of the meaning of the name Siloam merits our attention. The translation \223Sent\224 implies ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0645  Tc 0.6845  Tw (more than that the man was sent to the pool to find healing. We must rather observe that the pool was sent to him. ) Tj0 -11.52  TD 0  Tc 0.5995  Tw (For what ) Tj41.28 0  TD -0.0816  Tc 1.2053  Tw (does the act of this man in going to the pond mean in comparison with the healing that he finds in the ) Tj-41.28 -11.52  TD -0.0663  Tc 0.5607  Tw (water? The water reflects to him the image of Him who was sent by God to do the work of Him who sent Him. As ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0904  Tc 0.9304  Tw (the mud is an image of the suffering and dea) Tj183.84 0  TD -0.027  Tc 0.739  Tw (th of our Lord, so also is the water a picture of His resurrection. The ) Tj-183.84 -11.52  TD -0.0904  Tc -0.0296  Tw (victory of light over darkness took place at the dawn of \223the third day.\224 ) Tj283.2 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-247.2 -11.52  TD -0.0915  Tc 0.36  Tw (As fellow humans we can imagine how the man will have reacted to his healing. I would have wept for joy. ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.2659  Tc 2.0659  Tw (I su) Tj16.32 0  TD -0.0799  Tc 1.3465  Tw (ppose that his tears mingled with the mud and the water of Siloam. How overwhelming the experience must ) Tj-16.32 -11.52  TD -0.0694  Tc 0.7694  Tw (have been for him to see, for the first time in his life, the shapes, colors, and light in which our world daily bathes ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0348  Tc 0.8748  Tw (itself. It is the curse of those) Tj118.08 0  TD -0.0939  Tc 0.8379  Tw ( who can see that all we can see is ) Tj145.92 0  TD /F2 10.08  Tf0.0011  Tc 0.3589  Tw (d\351j\340 vu) Tj30.24 0  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0922  Tc 0.4522  Tw ( for us. We have changed from people who ) Tj-294.24 -11.52  TD -0.0891  Tc 0.6018  Tw (see to people who merely look. When this man washed the mud off his face, the feast began for him. His exuberant ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0548  Tc -0.0652  Tw (joy at that moment became the basis for all that follows.) Tj222.72 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-186.72 -11.52  TD 0.0811  Tc 0  Tw (T) Tj5.76 0  TD -0.0861  Tc 1.4343  Tw (he miracle of healing has taken place; what follows is both rather humoristic and intensely tragic. The ) Tj-41.76 -11.52  TD -0.1014  Tc 1.3974  Tw (reaction of the people in the streets and in the synagogue is highly laughable. John must have chuckled when he ) Tj0 -11.04  TD -0.0826  Tc 1.2106  Tw (wrote these verses. Something happened t) Tj170.88 0  TD -0.1163  Tc 0.9563  Tw (hat could not have happened. In a well) Tj157.92 0  TD 0.0034  Tc 0  Tw (-) Tj3.36 0  TD -0.0706  Tc 0.7186  Tw (ordered society that is disturbing. ) Tj-332.16 -11.52  TD -0.0747  Tc 0.4547  Tw (The same touch of divine humor can be found in the story of Jesus\222 walking on the water of the lake and the people ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0605  Tc 0.5805  Tw (in Capernaum trying to find out how He got there.) Tj204.96 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (352) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0651  Tc 0.3882  Tw ( It is even more hilarious when the tomb is opened after Jesus\222 ) Tj-215.04 -11.52  TD -0.0889  Tc 0.4489  Tw (resurrection and only the empty cocoon of Jesus\222 shroud is found. The Psalmist says: \223The One enthroned in heaven ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0843  Tc 0  Tw (laughs.\224) Tj32.64 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc (353) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0853  Tc 1.0126  Tw ( Our Lord poked fun at the neighbors and the Pharisees. ) Tj235.2 0  TD -0.1077  Tc 0.841  Tw (Those people are like cackling hens that find a ) Tj-277.92 -11.52  TD -0.066  Tc -0.054  Tw (diamond in their grains of corn. ) Tj127.68 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-91.68 -11.52  TD -0.1034  Tc 0.8929  Tw (It all began with the neighbors. They, of course, recognized the man but they could not believe their eyes. ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0954  Tc 1.4154  Tw (This prompted the man who was born blind to give his testimony. He) Tj290.4 0  TD -0.0458  Tc 1.1601  Tw ( could, however, not answer their question ) Tj-290.4 -11.52  TD -0.08  Tc 0.3486  Tw (where this Jesus could be found. He knew no more than what he had experienced himself. The spiritual lesson of his ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.06  Tc 1.4558  Tw (testimony lies in the development of his insight in the person of the Lord. His soul was ripe for ) Tj408.48 0  TD -0.0179  Tc 0.8579  Tw (the fullness of ) Tj-408.48 -11.52  TD -0.0912  Tc 0.3792  Tw (salvation only after Jesus revealed Himself personally to him as \223the Son of Man.\224 That was when the actual healing ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0712  Tc -0.0488  Tw (took place, of which the first was only a shadow. ) Tj195.84 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-15