ical and reasonable basis for our faith. Jesus\222 call for the fait) Tj268.32 0  TD -0.0185  Tc 1.1203  Tw (h of the people of His time was not illogical or ) Tj-268.32 -11.52  TD -0.083  Tc 1.4535  Tw (unreasonable. Every one could have understood that a man who heals people that are born blind and who raises ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0984  Tc -0.0216  Tw (people from the dead, speaks the truth when He claims to be sent by God. ) Tj292.32 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-256.32 -11.52  TD 0.0042  Tc 0.8358  Tw (With those words Jesus l) Tj102.72 0  TD -0.0437  Tc 0.5317  Tw (eads us further than the undeniable truth about His mission; He allows us to take ) Tj-138.72 -11.52  TD -0.059  Tc 0.6372  Tw (steps that increase the light for us. Faith comes from insight. In as much as we entrust ourselves to Him, the scales ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0642  Tc 0.4242  Tw (will fall from our eyes. Suspicion makes a person blind.) Tj225.6 0  TD -0.0934  Tc 0.2319  Tw ( If the Jews had not been so suspicious, they would have had ) Tj-225.6 -11.52  TD -0.064  Tc 0.496  Tw (no difficulty in accepting Jesus for what He claimed to be. The basis for their suspicion was their own unreliability. ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0231  Tc 2.0331  Tw (The person who, on the basis of his faith in God, puts his trust in Jesus, w) Tj325.92 0  TD -0.0491  Tc 1.6434  Tw (ill perceive that faith goes in two ) Tj-325.92 -11.52  TD -0.0744  Tc 0.5179  Tw (directions. It goes from us via the Father to the Son and via the Son to the Father. In that manner our understanding ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0636  Tc -0.0564  Tw (of the Father\222s character will increase.) Tj151.68 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-115.68 -11.52  TD -0.0886  Tc 1.0159  Tw (We can imagine what those words must have meant for those who) Tj273.6 0  TD -0.0627  Tc 0.7827  Tw ( saw Jesus before their eyes. For those ) Tj-309.6 -11.52  TD -0.1146  Tc 0.4986  Tw (who believed, they were the deepest truth ever expressed in human language. What do they